org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.localsearch

Class MatchingFrame

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.matchers.tuple.Tuple
      • org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.localsearch.MatchingFrame
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class MatchingFrame
extends Tuple
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    MatchingFrame represents the actual mappings of variables to constants. A MatchingFrame maintains a reference to its corresponding Pattern (or possibly flattened pattern). The following mappings are used by the interpreted engine:
    • VariableType => PatternVariable
    • ValueType => AnyModelElement

    • Method Detail

      • setKeys

        public boolean setKeys(int[] keys)
        The keys describes which elements of the frame corresponds to the parameters. The parameters are identified by the index, and a value might be added to multiple indexes in case of parameters made equal with a == constraint. As this array is different for each body instance, this method is called by the SearchPlanExecutor class later than initialization (done by the LocalSearchMatcher.
        Parameters:
        keys -
        Since:
        1.3
        See Also:
        #setParameterValues(Object[])} for setting the initial parameter

        public void setParameterValues(java.lang.Object[] parameterValues)
